On June 23, 2022, the President signed three bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 1170, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 1 League in Irvine, California, as the Tuskegee Airman Lieutenant Colonel Robert J. Friend Memorial Post Office Building. The second bill, H.R. 2324, designates the United States Postal Service facility at 2800 South Adams Street in Tallahassee, Florida, as the D. Edwina Stephens Post Office. The third bill, H.R. 4591, known as the VA Electronic Health Record Transparency Act of 2021, requires the Department of Veterans Affairs to submit periodic reports to Congress on various metrics of the VA's Electronic Health Record Modernization program. The President expressed gratitude to Representative Katie Porter and the bipartisan efforts of the California delegation for their leadership on H.R. 1170, Representative Al Lawson and the bipartisan efforts of the Florida delegation for H.R. 2324, and Representative Mrvan, Chair Takano, Ranking Member Bost, Chair Tester, Ranking Member Moran, and others for their leadership on H.R. 4591.